3Ô∏è‚É£ SINGLE-PAGE EXECUTIVE BRIEF (PDF TEXT)
BuzzIntell‚Ñ¢ ‚Äî Executive Overview
BuzzIntell‚Ñ¢ is a non-authoritative signal intelligence system designed to improve security, compliance, and automation outcomes by strictly separating perception from power.
BuzzIntell observes contextual and environmental signals and emits structured intelligence for downstream systems. It does not authenticate identities, enforce policy, access secrets, or execute actions.
By isolating intelligence from authorization and execution, BuzzIntell enables trust-zero architectures that reduce escalation risk, simplify compliance, and improve auditability.
This design supports SOC 2 and ISO 27001 principles by enforcing least privilege, clear trust boundaries, and verifiable separation of duties.
BuzzIntell does not replace IAM, policy engines, or enforcement layers. It strengthens them by ensuring intelligence cannot act on its own.
Perception first. Authority later.
